          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>In <fr:link href="/jms-00M6/" title="Lecture 18: surjections, injections, choice, and enumerability" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00M6/" display-uri="jms-00M6" type="local">Lecture 18</fr:link> we learned about <fr:link href="/jms-00MN/" title="Injective functions" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00MN/" display-uri="jms-00MN" type="local">injective</fr:link> and <fr:link href="/jms-00MF/" title="Surjective functions" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00MF/" display-uri="jms-00MF" type="local">surjective</fr:link> functions. In this section, we will see that <html:em>any</html:em> function <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  A\to  B]]></fr:tex> can be factored as the composition of a surjection followed by an injection.</html:p>
